# Chromium command-line flags for Edge Canary on Android
# Applied via /data/local/tmp/com.microsoft.emmx.canary-command-line
# Requires CommandLine file reading enabled (debuggable or smali patch)
#
# Memory optimization for mobile:
#   --process-per-site: share renderer across same-site tabs (vs per-tab)
#   --renderer-process-limit=4: hard cap on concurrent renderer processes
#   --js-flags: cap V8 old-space per renderer to prevent heap bloat
#
# REMOVED (caused content removal on pages + insecure):
#   --enable-low-end-device-mode: triggers aggressive OOM intervention that
#     strips page content ("To save memory, Edge removed some content")
#   --disable-site-isolation-trials: security warning + Spectre-vulnerable
#   IsolateOrigins,SitePerProcess: feature-flag equivalents of above
#
# OomIntervention: disables the in-page "removed some content" bar that
#   strips iframes/heavy elements when renderer memory gets high
#
# NOTE: --extension-process-limit=1 is intentionally excluded — sharing one
# renderer across uBlock, Dark Reader, Keepa, and CFC causes OOM crashes
# when combined V8 heaps exceed limits, killing all extensions at once.
#
--process-per-site
--renderer-process-limit=4
--disable-features=OomIntervention,MobileCopilot,MobileCopilotButton,MobileCopilotChat,OmniboxPedalSuggestionsUi,EdgeCopilot,EdgeCopilotChat,EdgeCopilotNewTabPageCard,EdgeDiscoverFeed,msEdgeCopilotEntryPointsOverall,msEdgeCopilotSystemtray
--js-flags=--max-old-space-size=256
--load-extension=/data/local/tmp/cfc-ext
#
# Extension sideloading:
#   --load-extension: load unpacked CFC extension from device storage
#   Requires extension files pushed to /data/local/tmp/cfc-ext/
#
# AI/Copilot removal:
#   MobileCopilot/Button/Chat: toolbar Copilot button + chat sidebar
#   OmniboxPedalSuggestionsUi: AI suggestions in address bar
#   EdgeCopilot/Chat/NewTabPageCard: desktop-origin Copilot features
#   EdgeDiscoverFeed: news/AI feed on new tab page
#   msEdgeCopilotEntryPointsOverall/Systemtray: additional Copilot UI entry points
